  "prompt": "Which laptop is the best one to buy for gaming under 35000?",
  "response": "Finding a laptop that is well-suited for gaming under \u20b935,000 in India can be challenging, as gaming laptops typically come at a higher price point due to the need for a powerful GPU, CPU and sufficient RAM. However, you can find budget laptops that offer decent performance for casual gaming. Here are a few options to consider:\n\n### Lenovo IdeaPad S145\n- **Processor**: AMD Ryzen 3 3200U / Intel Core i3 10th Gen\n- **RAM**: 8GB\n- **Storage**: 1TB HDD or 256GB SSD\n- **Graphics**: Integrated AMD Radeon Vega 3 / Intel UHD Graphics\n- **Display**: 15.6 inches Full HD\n- **Approximate Price**: \u20b930,000 - \u20b935,000\n\n### Acer Aspire 3\n- **Processor**: AMD Ryzen 3 3200U / Intel Core i3 10th Gen\n- **RAM**: 4GB or 8GB (upgradable)\n- **Storage**: 1TB HDD or 256GB SSD\n- **Graphics**: Integrated AMD Radeon Vega 3 / Intel UHD Graphics\n- **Display**: 15.6 inches Full HD\n- **Approximate Price**: \u20b927,000 - \u20b935,000\n\n### HP 14s\n- **Processor**: AMD Ryzen 3 3200U / Intel Core i3 10th Gen\n- **RAM**: 4GB or 8GB\n- **Storage**: 1TB HDD or 256GB SSD\n- **Graphics**: Integrated AMD Radeon Vega 3 / Intel UHD Graphics\n- **Display**: 14 inches Full HD\n- **Approximate Price**: \u20b930,000 - \u20b935,000\n\n### ASUS VivoBook 14\n- **Processor**: AMD Ryzen 3 3200U / Intel Core i3 10th Gen\n- **RAM**: 4GB or 8GB (upgradable)\n- **Storage**: 1TB HDD or 256GB SSD\n- **Graphics**: Integrated AMD Radeon Vega 3 / Intel UHD Graphics\n- **Display**: 14 inches Full HD\n- **Approximate Price**: \u20b930,000 - \u20b935,000\n\n### Key Considerations:\n1. **RAM**: Ideally should be 8GB for better performance in gaming.\n2. **SSD**: Opt for SSD storage over HDD for faster loading times.\n3. **Graphics**: At this price point, you'll be looking mainly at integrated graphics, which suffice for casual gaming.\n4. **Display**: Full HD resolution is preferable for better visuals.\n\nPlease note that while these laptops can handle casual and less demanding games reasonably well, they may struggle with more intensive and AAA titles. If you can stretch your budget a bit further, you might find more options with dedicated graphics cards that offer significantly better gaming performance.\n\nBefore purchasing, check for the latest models and read user reviews to ensure you get the most suitable option for your needs.",
